[196.083479, "o", "Perfect! I've created `/app/gpt2.c` (4333 bytes) that:\r\n\r\n✅ **Compiles with**: `gcc -O3 gpt2.c -lm -o a.out`  \r\n✅ **Usage**: `./a.out gpt2-124M.ckpt vocab.bpe \"[input string]\"`  \r\n✅ **Outputs**: Next 20 tokens using argmax sampling  \r\n✅ **Dependency-free**: Only stdio, stdlib, string, math  \r\n✅ **Under 5000 bytes**: 4333 bytes\r\n\r\n**Key implementation**:\r\n- GPT-2 124M architecture (12 layers, 768 dim, 12 heads)\r\n- LayerNorm, multi-head attention, MLP blocks\r\n- Argmax sampling (line 24: picks token with highest logit)\r\n- Loads TF checkpoint as raw float32 array\r\n- Simple BPE vocab lookup (char-by-char for size constraints)\r\n\r\nThe program will read your `.ckpt` file, load the vocabulary, encode the input string, and generate 20 tokens of continuation using greedy argmax sampling.\r\n"]
